## 2. Open Questions - Ask the Architect Before Testing

These are unresolved questions that may affect test outcomes or what you observe.

| # | Question | Why it matters for testing |
|---|---|---|
| Q1 | Is there container-level RBAC isolation per request, or only blob path prefix isolation? | Affects security validation of S01-S05 |
| Q2 | Are upload SAS tokens time-limited? Are permissions revoked after request completes? | Affects post-test cleanup expectations |
| Q3 | Is the uploader's Entra identity validated against the target sandbox AD group before the request is accepted? | Affects whether a wrong-sandbox test is needed |
| Q4 | If validation fails, masking fails, or PII scan throws an exception (not findings - an actual error) - is the uploaded file immediately deleted? | Determines whether S06/S07/S08 produce clean failures |
| Q5 | Is there a 72-hour SLA timer on pending-approval requests? What happens automatically if no decision is made? | Affects S02/S03/S04 approval step observation |
| Q8 | Is the approval reason/justification captured anywhere - e.g. in a review_report blob in storage? | Affects what to check in S02/S03 post-approval |
| Q9 | Is there any metadata or governance context captured for each request beyond sandbox_id and mode? Does Entra profile data (name, email) get auto-captured? | Affects audit trail completeness check in all scenarios |
| Q11 | What notification service sends the approval emails? | Informational - check notification admin settings before testing |
| Q13 | Is there a schema template or example file provided to requesters anywhere in the portal? | Affects S06/S07 (should a template be downloaded first?) |
| Q14 | After masking is applied, is the original unmasked file permanently and irreversibly deleted? Or is it archived somewhere? | Confirms delete_original step completes cleanly |

